> Ready in less than 25 minutes, this Speedy Cajun Chicken and Bacon Macaroni is quick and full of flavour. Punchy and smoky with a spicy kick, Cajun spice mix contains ingredients such as chilli powder, ground cumin, oregano and thyme.

Boil a full #kettle{}.

Peel and grate the @garlic clove{2}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

Pour the boiled water into a large #saucepan{} with @salt{1/2%tsp} on high heat.

Stir the @macaroni{180%g} into the water and bring back to the boil. Cook until
tender, ~{12%minutes}.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the @diced British chicken breast{240%g} to the pan and season with
@salt{} and @pepper{}.

Fry until golden brown on the outside and cooked through, ~{8-10%minutes}.
Halfway through, add the @British smoked bacon lardons{90%g} to the pan and
stir-fry, ~{4-5%minutes}. IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after
handling raw chicken and its packaging. It's cooked when no longer pink in the
middle. Cook bacon thoroughly.

Once the chicken is cooked through, reduce the heat to medium and add the
garlic, @tomato puree{30%g} and @Cajun spice mix{1%sachet} (add less if you'd
prefer things milder). Stir-fry for ~{1%minute}.

Stir in the @chicken stock paste{10%g}, @creme fraiche{150%g}, @water{100%ml}
and half the @grated hard Italian style cheese{20%g}. Bring to the boil.

Lower the heat and simmer until slightly thickened, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Meanwhile, once the macaroni is cooked, drain in a #colander{} and pop back into
the pan.

Drizzle with @oil{} and stir through to stop it sticking together.

Add the @baby spinach{40%g} to the chicken pan a handful at a time until
wilted and piping hot, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Stir through the cooked macaroni. Taste and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}
if needed. Add a splash of water if you feel it needs it.

Remove from the heat.

Share the Cajun macaroni between your #serving bowls{}.

Sprinkle over the remaining cheese to finish. Enjoy!